RIGOBERT SAYS is a fast, addictive memory game with a royal twist — inspired by the classic Simon Says, but taken further.

A disc lights up coloured buttons in a sequence — your job is to repeat it exactly, even as the sequence grows longer and the challenge increases.

Unlike Simon Says, multiple buttons can light up at the same time, and you must press them simultaneously. More colours, more combinations, more to remember.

🔴 🟢 🔵  Three colours that mix — press Red and Green together and the disc glows Yellow. Red and Blue makes Magenta. All three at once: White.

Want more challenge? Make the disc FLOAT across the screen, SPIN as you play, or turn on BOTH at once. The harder the mode, the greater the glory.

👑  Four difficulty modes:
- STILL — classic, focused gameplay
- FLOAT — the disc drifts around the screen
- SPIN — the disc slowly rotates as you play
- BOTH — floating and spinning at the same time

🏆  Personal records tracked separately for each mode — can you top your best on every difficulty?

🎵  Each button combination plays a unique musical note, turning the sequence into a melody you have to remember.

Simple to learn. Surprisingly hard to master. No ads. No nonsense.
